			"type": "text",
			"text": "Kettneraspis is a genus of spiny trilobite found worldwide, ranging from the Ordovician to the Devonian. It was a rather small trilobite, growing to three centimeters in length. Like other odontopleurids it would've likely either used its spines for protection or to attract a mate. It has been proposed that this animal was sexually dimorphic, however it is likely this is merely just individual variation."
